Furthermore, Idea 1’s focus on modeling *explanation modality efficacy* goes beyond optimization of annotation strategy—it rethinks the very structure of human evaluation protocols in XAI. This level of adaptivity and cognitive respect has not been explored in the cited papers, which mostly focus on generating contrastive explanations rather than intelligently selecting when to deploy them.

Thus, while both ideas are strong, **Idea 1** demonstrates greater novelty by challenging a core assumption in the field (ubiquitous contrastivity), aligning with and extending the implications of Paper 1, and proposing a fundamentally new architecture for human-in-the-loop evaluation.

